<?xml version="1.0"?>
<report xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"
        xmlns="http://jfreereport.sourceforge.net/namespaces/reports/flow">
  <query>default</query>
  <configuration>
    <property name="org.jfree.report.modules.output.pageable.pdf.Encoding">IDENTITY-H</property>
  </configuration>
  <datasource href="sample.sqlds"/>

  <expression class="org.jfree.report.function.aggregation.ItemCountFunction">
    <name>RowCount</name>
    <property name="precompute">true</property>
  </expression>

  <expression class="org.jfree.report.function.aggregation.ItemCountFunction">
    <name>RowCount</name>
  </expression>

  <page-header>
    This is my page header. JFreeReport will place the content defined here
    somewhere outside of the normal document flow.
  </page-header>

  All the stuff here up to the group tag is put into the report header.

  <section>
    <display-condition class="org.jfree.report.function.sys.IsEmptyDataExpression"/>
    Sorry, there is no data given.
    <html:div style="font-face: serif">
      <attribute name="test">Test</attribute>
      <html:a href="/error.jsp">Go ask your administrator!</html:a>
    </html:div>
  </section>

  <group>
    <grouping-expression>
      <property name="field[0]">group_arg_1</property>
    </grouping-expression>
    <display-condition class="org.jfree.report.function.sys.IsNotEmptyDataExpression"/>
    <operation-before operation="mark"/>

    This is a group. The text following the open group tag is placed into the
    group header.

    <group>
      <!-- this class is also the default value for the class attribute.. -->
      <grouping-expression class="org.jfree.report.function.sys.GroupByExpression">
        <property name="field[0]">Continent</property>
      </grouping-expression>

      A nested group.
      <content>
        <value-expression>
          <property name="field">Country</property>
        </value-expression>
      </content>

      <section repeat="true">
        <operation-before operation="advance"/>
        Thats the left over from my Itemband.
        <content>
          <value-expression>
            <property name="field">Continent</property>
          </value-expression>
        </content>
        <content>
          <value-expression>
            <property name="field">Country</property>
          </value-expression>
        </content>
        <content>
          <value-expression>
            <property name="field">Population</property>
          </value-expression>
        </content>
      </section>

      The nested group's footer.
      <content>
        <value-expression>
          <property name="field">Country</property>
        </value-expression>
      </content>

    </group>

    <group>
      <grouping-expression>
        <property name="field[0]">group_argument_2</property>
      </grouping-expression>
      <operation-before operation="recall"/>

      A nested paralell group. Given a clean way to control the cursor
      (attribute 'cursor="reset"') this allows us to traverse the same
      data twice.
      <detail-section>
        Thats the left over from my Itemband.
        <content>
          <value-expression>
            <property name="field">Continent</property>
          </value-expression>
        </content>
        <content>
          <value-expression>
            <property name="field">Population</property>
          </value-expression>
        </content>
      </detail-section>
      The nested group's footer.
    </group>

    As usual, all text after the detail section makes up the group footer.
  </group>

  <page-footer>
    This is my page footer. JFreeReport will place the content defined here
    somewhere outside of the normal document flow.
  </page-footer>

  Everything after the group or detail section is placed into the report footer.

  <html:img src="gorilla.jpg" alt="Gorilla"/>
</report>
